Image sourced from the Cotton Festival website.This year, Cotton Fest will feature over 130 of South Africa’s finest musical talents. The festival will merge both well-known and young emerging South African artists over three stages.The confirmed weekend line-up includes Candii, Gemini Major, Frank Casino, Busta 929, Indigo Stella, Cassper Nyovest, DJ Kaymo, Khanyisa, Lady Du and many more.Image supplied: The Cotton Festival lineupPlease note that the Cotton Fest line-up is subject to change prior to the show.The weekend will include various other lifestyle elements to keep all cotton eaters entertained. Some of the cool things cotton eaters can enjoy on-site will be, a games area, a super cool food court, a live skating competition, a Cotton Fest and Puma customization station, a Retail fashion ‘tuckshop’ featuring Cotton Fest merch and other limited edition clothing items will be available for sale. There will also be a half-court and live art to engage with on-site.Cotton Festival postponed to later this year9 Mar 2022MTVBase returns as a media partner alongside YFM for the 2022 edition of Cotton Fest.Phase 2 tickets will be available via Webtickets and Pick 'n Pay outlets nationwide from 1 April. Cotton Fest will take place from 23-24 April at The Station, Carr Street and Nelson Mandela Bridge, Newtown, Johannesburg. The day pass costs R300.